Two Indians and an African man have been arrested by the Narcotics Control Bureau (NCB) here in connection with a party drug trafficking case, a senior official said today He said about a kilogram of various drugs — 215 g of methamphetamine, 180 g of cocaine and 415 g of heroin — have been seized by the agency after searches were conducted in the Uttam Nagar and Mohan Garden area of the national capital. The agency did not reveal the identities of the three men who were arrested but said the two Indians were first intercepted on the basis of prior inputs which led them to the African man who allegedly provided them the drugs after sourcing them from Africa. “The three people were part of an inter-state drug syndicate operating in Delhi, the national capital region and Punjab,” the NCB official said. 0 comments Do you get a good or bad response from your wife after making love? Discover a great natural solution that changed my story and put an end to weak/premature ejaculation, CLICK HERE. 